
@startuml

' Classes involved in the Helping Hands Store system

class Resident {
  - name: String
  - streetAddress: String
  - phoneNumber: String
  - email: String (optional)
  - itemsDescription: String
}

class PickupRequest {
  - id: Integer
  - pickupTime: Time (8:00 to 14:00)
  - status: String (e.g., scheduled, completed)
  - resident: Resident
  - pickupDate: Date
}

class VolunteerDriver {
  - id: Integer
  - name: String
  - availableDays: List<Date>
  - vehicle: PickupVehicle
}

class PickupVehicle {
  - id: Integer
  - licensePlate: String
  - storageCapacity: Integer (in kg)
  - currentLoad: Integer (in kg)
  - route: Route
}

class Route {
  - id: Integer
  - pickupRequests: List<PickupRequest>
  - startTime: Time
  - endTime: Time
  - driver: VolunteerDriver
}

class DistributionCenter {
  - id: Integer
  - address: String
  - employees: List<Employee>
}

class Employee {
  - id: Integer
  - name: String
  - role: String (e.g., inventory manager, delivery assistant)
  - distributionCenter: DistributionCenter
}

class SecondHandItem {
  - id: Integer
  - description: String
  - category: String (from list of 134 categories)
  - rfidTagId: String
  - condition: String (e.g., good, damaged)
  - pickupRequest: PickupRequest
}

class FoodItem {
  - id: Integer
  - description: String
  - pickupRequest: PickupRequest
}

class FoodBank {
  - id: Integer
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class DeliveryRequest {
  - id: Integer
  - client: Client
  - item: SecondHandItem
  - deliveryDate: Date
  - deliveryTime: Time
  - status: String (e.g., pending, delivered)
}

class Client {
  - id: Integer
  - name: String
  - address: String
  - preferredCategories: List<String>
  - distributionCenter: DistributionCenter
}

' Relationships

Resident "1" --> "0..*" PickupRequest : submits
PickupRequest "1" --> "1" VolunteerDriver : assigned to
VolunteerDriver "1" --> "1" PickupVehicle : drives
PickupVehicle "1" --> "1" Route : has
Route "1" --> "0..*" PickupRequest : includes
PickupRequest "1" --> "1" SecondHandItem : generates
PickupRequest "1" --> "1" FoodItem : generates

DistributionCenter "1" --> "0..*" Employee : employs
Employee "1" --> "0..*" SecondHandItem : inspects and tags
Employee "1" --> "0..*" DeliveryRequest : handles

SecondHandItem "1" --> "1" DistributionCenter : stored at
FoodItem "1" --> "1" FoodBank : delivered to

Client "1" --> "0..*" DeliveryRequest : receives
Client "1" --> "1" DistributionCenter : registered with

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Resident**: The person requesting a pickup.
- **PickupRequest**: Represents a request for a pickup by a resident.
- **VolunteerDriver & PickupVehicle**: Volunteers who drive vehicles to collect items.
- **Route**: A sequence of pickups for a given day and vehicle.
- **DistributionCenter**: Where second-hand items are processed.
- **Employee**: Handles quality checks, tagging, and delivery arrangements.
- **SecondHandItem & FoodItem**: Types of collected items.
- **FoodBank**: Where food items are dropped off.
- **Client**: Individuals receiving second-hand items via delivery.
- **DeliveryRequest**: Manages delivery requests for clients unable to visit.

